   <abstract displayLabel="Description">The Graflex Century 35 was made by Kowa in Japan and imported by Graflex to USA. It is a 35mm camera. The lens is Kowa Opt. Works Prominar F.C. f/3.5, 45mm; shutter speeds B. 1-1/500.  From 1905 to 1926 the company was a division of Eastman Kodak in Rochester, New York. When a court had ordered that Kodak had to sell its Folmer &amp; Schwing division no buyers appeared. A new company was founded which was named Folmer Graflex Corporation in 1928. In 1945 it was renamed to Graflex Inc.. From the days of depression of the 1930s to 1957 the company grew from 100 to 760 employees. It made successfully sophisticated SLRs and press cameras as well as TLRs and several 35mm cameras.</abstract>
